result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Case called @ 1:46 p.m. Defendant Bruce L. Vossekuil in court with attorney Ben Szilagyi.  Defendant Bruce L. Vossekuil in custody.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. The Court entertains waiver of the preliminary hearing. The Court accepts voluntary waiver of the preliminary hearing. Defendant BOT. Information filed. Receipt admitted - Reading waived. Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea: Ct 1 - NC. Repeater enhancer DRI.  Court accepts plea and enters JOC. 15CM278 - DRI. Sentencing argument by DA Blader. Sentencing argument by Atty Szilagyi. No statement by DE. Court orders: 2 year term of imprisonment consecutive to any other sentence currently being served to include but not limited to Wood Co Case 05CF505 and Adams Co Case 05CF111 - Bifurcated SEH - 1 yr IC/ 1 yr ES - 256 days CFTS. ES Conditions: Any terms or conditions as deemed appropriate by supervising agent, NC w/ J. Rozner, Restitution in the amount of $200, Costs to be paid from up to 25% of inmate earnings during IC. Defendant is not eligible for CIP or SAP.  Appeal rights given.
